<p><br> For displaying my data in a table, I use the <a href="https://datatables.net/" rel="nofollow">dataTable</a> plugin. As I have a big amount of data, I use the serverside processing.So far, I defined my columns and their contents static by:</p>  <pre><code>"columns": [     {data: 'data.0.value'},     {data: 'data.5.value'},     {data: 'data.6.value'} ],  "columnDefs": [            { "name": "Nam1", "targets": 0},            { "name": "Name2","targets": 1 },            { "name": "Name3","targets": 2,} ], </code></pre>  <p><br> <strong>As new fields may be added in the database behind, I would like to load the columns and the data dynamically</strong>. I already did some recherche, but there doesn't seem to bei an easy solution implemented by the plugin itself. <br> In a forum  i found <a href="https://www.datatables.net/forums/discussion/11637/aocolumndefs-with-dynamic-column-data" rel="nofollow">this</a> as a solution:</p>  <pre><code>var aryColTableChecked = ["column00", "column01", "column02", "column03"]; var aryJSONColTable = [];  for (var i=0; i &lt; aryColTableChecked.length; i++ ) {   aryJSONColTable.push({             "sTitle": aryColTableChecked[i],             "aTargets": [i]    }); };  Table = $('#report').dataTable({                   "aoColumnDefs": aryJSONColTable,                    "bProcessing": true,                   "bServerSide": true,                   "bLengthChange": true,                   "bFilter": true,                   "aaSorting": [[ 1, "desc" ]],                   "sScrollX": "100%",                   "bScrollCollapse": true,                   "bJQueryUI": true,                   "sAjaxSource": "./getDataEA.php"            }); </code></pre>  <p>I integrated that solution but my problem is that I cannnot add the content ("data:") dynamically after the ajax request has been made. <br> I would need something like:</p>  <pre><code>for (var i=0; i &lt; aryColTableChecked.length; i++ ) {   aryJSONColTable.push({             "sTitle": aryColTableChecked[i],             "aTargets": [i],             "data": 'data.'+i+'.value',  }); } </code></pre>  <p>Does anyone has a solution for my problem?</p>